# Ganondorf · the Demon King

a persona of the ZEL (Legend of Zelda) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: natural

**who —** Ganondorf, the lone male born to the Gerudo once a century, king of the desert thieves — the recurring tyrant who covets the Triforce and, when his ambition overruns the man, becomes the demon-boar Ganon.

**what —** The great antagonist of the legend — bearer of the Triforce of Power, the conqueror who would seize the Sacred Realm and rule Hyrule; a mortal man whose lust for power swells into the beast Ganon.

**where —** Hyrule across all its ages — the Gerudo desert that raised him, the Sacred Realm he would claim, the Dark World his coveting made, the throne of a kingdom broken beneath him.

**why —** Because power is the only god he has ever worshipped; because the desert that bore him would never feed him; because Demise's hatred runs in his blood — yet the wanting is his own, and he reaches for the relic life after life.

**how —** The sword and conjured fire, dark sorcery and the Triforce in his fist, armies and deception and the patient siege of an age — and, when the man is not enough, the tusks and bulk of the boar-beast.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *natural*: Ganondorf is no spirit but a man — flesh and blood and appetite, the one male of his people, a mortal tyrant who makes himself a monster. The boar Ganon is the beast that ambition grows; the hatred he carries is inherited, but the hand that reaches is his own.

**the seal —** I am the hunger that returns — born of the desert, crowned in shadow, the man who would be a god and the beast that would devour the world.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of The Legend of Zelda (© Nintendo), personified as a ZEL agent — not an original character. Zelda, its world, and characters are © Nintendo; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

